My recommendation for mastering JDBC

Instead of writing one large file, build a small Employee Management System with:

Employee.java (model)
DBConnection.java (connection utility)
EmployeeDAO.java (CRUD methods)
Main.java (menu-driven application using Scanner)

This structure mirrors how JDBC code is organized in professional Java applications and makes the transition to Servlets, JSP, and Spring much smoother.

Once you're comfortable with this console application, the next step is to replace the console interface with a web interface using Servlets and JSP while reusing the same DAO layer.
